Kia ora Grant,

Thank you for your email and for confirming receipt of our letter.

Friday, 17 October after 2:00 pm works for me, and I=E2=80=99d =
appreciate it if testing and assessment could be scheduled accordingly.

I also reserve my right to undertake independent testing and assessment =
of the property to ensure a full and impartial evaluation.

Having reviewed the proposed plan, I=E2=80=99m concerned the current =
testing schedule appears incomplete. It does not include the first =
floor, roof cavity, or the large upper deck, and the basement coverage =
seems partial, given the known extent of smoke, water, and chemical =
contamination.

I therefore request confirmation that the planned inspection and =
sampling will be expanded to include all levels and relevant structural =
areas. Alternatively, please confirm that Tower will meet my reasonable =
costs should I need to arrange independent specialists to carry out =
supplementary testing (including laboratory analysis).

Please confirm the final timing for the 17th and the revised scope of =
testing once available.

Ng=C4=81 mihi,
Raffaella


> On 8 Oct 2025, at 5:26=E2=80=AFPM, Grant Metson =
<Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz> wrote:
>=20
> Hello Raffaella and Abigail,
> Thank you for the letter received yesterday at 4:35
> I am replying to acknowledge receipt of the letter, and to further =
acknowledge that Abigail will be copied into all correspondence moving =
forward.
> I have requested that the appointed specialists provide dates and =
times when they can be available.
> I am proposing that the following persons complete site visit, =
assessing & testing, as a necessary pre-requisite to providing relevant =
reports for all stakeholders to review:
> =20
> Grant Metson =E2=80=93 Regional Assessing Manager
> Stephen Walker =E2=80=93 Technical Building Consultant. ASURNZ.
> Warwick Banks =E2=80=93 Associate Structural Engineer. CPEng
> Alexandra Dalzell =E2=80=93 Forensic Scientist
> Tyrell Craig =E2=80=93 Restoration Cleaning Specialist.
> LBP Builder [ unconfirmed individual ] =E2=80=93 we will require the =
builder to cut inspection holes in the wall linings so testing can be =
completed within the wall cavities.
> =20
> The intention is to test for smoke and chemical contamination within =
the wall cavities, and on the exposed surfaces downstairs. There will be =
a significant number of sample sites [tests] to be completed to be able =
to author a reliable report. After initial testing is completed, our =
intention is to apply restorative cleaning methods to targeted =
individual sample sites, followed by subsequent testing, post-cleaning, =
to provide data to measure the effectiveness of =
cleaning/decontamination.
> All samples taken from site will require laboratory analysis before =
being incorporated into a report. This process may take up to 10 working =
days =E2=80=93 so we want to capture swab samples from surfaces before =
and after the decontamination process is undertaken.
> =20
> At this stage we are looking like being able to conduct this testing =
onsite, as well as CPEng site visit for assessment, on Friday October =
17. Time to yet be confirmed.
> =20
> I am unsure from your letter attached whether Raffaella and/or other =
nominated parties wish to be present while this testing and assessment =
is being conducted. Can you please confirm for me so that I can complete =
arrangements that will suit all parties who need to be present.
> =20
> Many Thanks,
> Grant.
> =20
